Actor Ime Bishop Umoh aka Okon Lagos has leaped for joy over the government’s decision to purchase lie detecting machines. Wishing the machines will be bought and deployed during the campaign ahead of the 2023 general elections, the comedian applauded the government for the initiative noting it was the best project they’ll ever embark on. “Best project this government will ever embark on is that of LIE DETECTING MACHINES. I was overjoyed when I heard it is in the offing. “I wish it can be bought and used especially for election campaign promises ahead of 2023!   Uche Maduagwu slams Kpokpogiri over Tonto Dikeh     Banky W joins PDP, guns for House of Reps seat     Cardi B absent at Grammys, deletes Twitter account over…   “I heard government wants to but LIE DETECTING MACHINES. Can U suggest respectfully person(s), agency(ies) that initiative won’t favor?” he added. The Federal Executive Council (FEC) approved N1 billion for the purchase of lie detector scanner and night vision glasses for the National Drug Law Enforcement Agency (NDLEA). The Attorney-General of the Federation and Minister of Justice, Abubakar Malami made this known to journalists on Wednesday, March 30 in Abuja after the weekly FEC meeting. According to Mr Malami, the devices would go a long way in aiding the agency in the work it is already doing of fight against drug abuse. He said the approvals were given after the council approved two memos whose contracts were awarded to two tech companies.